Staffs are friendly!! They explained everything to us patiently! Service is excellent! Dessert is the bomb! Definitely worth a revisit!

tip.text: Rating: 5.5/10.They only have 3 main courses.Thai basil rice is just okay (nothing special) and it costs 7.90 for that small portion.Pork neck is just not crispy at all.Overall: pricy and so-so.
Their chicken & waffle is da bomb! The chicken is so crunchy! I like the concept of pairing with fruits especially it goes well with orange! Savory + sweet (abit sour). Definitely worth a revisit! 💕
Their Leong shui is fine but i can't found any 蓮子 (六味涼水 supposed to have 蓮子?! Hmm) Royak tastes okay but there's no mango which is quite disappointed.

tip.text: I love their waffle and ice cream! Salted caramel is so good!
Give it a try to their craft beer (hazelnut) and it is so good! I like their burger (the champ), bun is really soft!
Good service! Serve water without having to request it! Cake is cute and taste great. Get to have strawberry and lychee in every single bite! Love it!
Friendly service! amazing concept of savory crepe! Shore to please is great as well as sweet potato fries!
I love their service.you know they care of their food quality when they ask 'how's the food? Is everything okay?' Had the dark herbal soup and it is really good! Papaya salad is hella spicy and hot!
Absolute loving salted caramel molten cake!
